## 5. Edge Function — API Contract

### Endpoint
`POST /functions/v1/seed-master-data`

### Request
```typescript
interface SeedRequest {
  tenant_id: string;
  user_id: string;
  profile_type?: 'seller' | 'buyer';       // default: read from t_tenant_profiles
  industry_id?: string;                     // default: read from t_tenant_profiles
  target_industries?: string[];             // default: read from t_tenant_served_industries
  nomenclatures?: string[];                 // seller only
  options?: {
    skip_categories?: boolean;
    skip_catalog?: boolean;
    skip_blocks?: boolean;
    skip_events?: boolean;
    dry_run?: boolean;
  };
}
```

### Response
```typescript
interface SeedResponse {
  success: boolean;
  tenant_id: string;
  profile_type: 'seller' | 'buyer';
  industry_id: string;
  served_industries: string[];
  seeded: {
    category_masters: number;
    category_details: number;
    catalog_industries: number;
    event_statuses: number;
    // Seller
    catalog_categories?: number;
    resource_templates?: number;
    service_equipment_blocks?: number;
    client_asset_types?: number;
    // Buyer
    equipment_registry?: number;
    facility_registry?: number;
    cross_domain_equipment?: number;
    procurement_categories?: number;
  };
  errors?: string[];
}
```

### Flow
```
Request → Verify tenant → Read profile_type, industry_id, served_industries from DB
  ↓
Common: Step A (categories) → Step B (industries) → Step C (event statuses)
  ↓
Branch:
  SELLER → S1 (catalog categories) → S2 (resources) → S3 (block matrix) → S4 (client assets)
  BUYER  → B1 (equipment + facility registry) → B2 (vendor + procurement categories)
  ↓
Return counts
```

